			<p class="entry-summary">The games we love also love us back &mdash; mostly, by reflecting our successes and failures in delicious ways. This talk will explore the concept of feedback in game design, using examples drawn from both personal &amp; professional experience. We’ll examine a variety of feedback mechanisms (good and bad), and discuss how lessons drawn from these examples can be applied to any user experience. <a href="juicyfeedback">Transcript</a></p>
